<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1814,2093]" lastBlockId="12.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">
The specimens were collected twice in 
<collectingRegion box="[590,658,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, in the municipality of Pirenópolis (Morro do Frota near Meia Ponte and Serra do Arruda), and once in the 
<collectingRegion box="[573,750,1850,1876]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
(Chapadinha). The two varieties described by Otto von Berg, 
<taxonomicName box="[136,550,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="goyazensis" variety="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[136,550,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia goyazensis var. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[615,934,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="goyazensis" variety="latifolia">
<emphasis box="[615,934,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. goyazensis var. latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, O." box="[954,1086,1886,1913]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 656" refId="ref13590" refString="Berg, O. (1857 - 1859) Myrtaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 14, pt. 1. Frid. Fleischer in Comm., Lipsiae [Leipzig] &amp; Monachii [Munich], pp. 1 - 656. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book chapter" year="1857">Berg, 1857</bibRefCitation>
–1859: 188) have already been synonymised to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Govaerts et al. 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Govaerts" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[318,731,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis box="[318,476,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. goyazensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Ashton, P. &amp; Barrie, F. &amp; Holst, B. K. &amp; Landrum, L. R. &amp; Matsumoto, K. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Nic Lughadha, E. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. H. &amp; Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E. J." box="[491,723,1922,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" refId="ref14573" refString="Govaerts, R., Sobral, M., Ashton, P., Barrie, F., Holst, B. K., Landrum, L. R., Matsumoto, K., Mazine, F. F., Nic Lughadha, E., Proenca, C. E. B., Soares-Silva, L. H., Wilson, P. G., Lucas, E. J. (2020) World Checklist of Myrtaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet: http: // wcsp. science. kew. org / (accessed 26 October 2020)" type="url" year="2020">
Govaerts 
<emphasis box="[600,656,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The Saint-Hilaire specimen (
<typeStatus box="[1061,1111,1922,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1354,1923,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis box="[1147,1354,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the Glaziou specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[383,580,1959,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis box="[383,580,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[593,748,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arrudeana">
<emphasis box="[593,748,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. arrudeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[801,1025,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis box="[801,1025,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all from the “Serra dos Pyreneos”. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,385,1995,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis box="[136,385,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[402,559,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arrudeana">
<emphasis box="[402,559,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. arrudeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[618,845,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis box="[618,845,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar variability of leaf size and shape to the aforementioned species and they all share the same leaf venation pattern, inflorescence 
<typeStatus box="[1103,1151,2031,2057]" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
and indumentum. 
<bibRefCitation author="Legrand, C. D. &amp; Mattos, J. R." pageId="11" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref15062" refString="Legrand, C. D. &amp; Mattos, J. R. 1975. Novidades taxonomicas em Myrtaceae. Loefgrenia 67: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1975">Legrand &amp; Mattos (1975)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName box="[467,715,2067,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meiapontensis">
<emphasis box="[467,715,2067,2092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">Myrcia meiapontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[894,1120,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chapadinhaeana">
<emphasis box="[894,1120,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="80">M. chapadinhaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The collections are all quite similar as to the shapes, sizes and venation patterns of the leaves, as well as inflorescence and indumentum. This species is now quite well known, with dozens of modern collections of 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1095,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis box="[936,1095,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="81">M. goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in HEPH and UB.
